						<div class="postbody">Yes, but according to this:
<br /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Frame interrupt flag is set three times in a row 29831 clocks after writing $00 to $4017.</div>
<br />
<br />In other words, yup, the PPU takes 341*262/3 CPU cycles per frame, but the APU doesn't rely in such timing (frame IRQs).</div>

					
